# OT Sentinel — Allowed Non-Standard Modbus Ports CDB List
# ======================================================
# Format: PORT:Description
#
# This list suppresses false positives for rule 200011 (OT-SENTINEL-MOD-008)
# which alerts on Modbus traffic on any port other than 502.
#
# Some legitimate Modbus deployments use non-standard ports:
# - Modbus gateways often use port 1502
# - NAT/port-forwarding setups may remap ports
# - Legacy devices may have hardcoded alternate ports
#
# Deployment: Copy to /var/ossec/etc/lists/ and add to ossec.conf:
#   <list>etc/lists/non_standard_modbus_ports</list>
#
# Usage in rule (if you want to suppress known ports):
#   <list field="destination_port" lookup="not_match_key">etc/lists/non_standard_modbus_ports</list>

# Common legitimate non-standard Modbus ports
1502:Modbus_Gateway_Default
1503:Modbus_Gateway_Alternate
2502:Modbus_Alternate

